where the close button is.

01:16:11.610 --> 01:16:11.850
Good one.

01:16:11.990 --> 01:16:12.640
Feedback error.

01:16:12.640 --> 01:16:13.940
It's just a funny joke.

01:16:14.010 --> 01:16:14.380
Come on.

01:16:14.400 --> 01:16:18.180
So this is poor communication,
but it's okay.

01:16:18.180 --> 01:16:19.750
I mean, you know,
I wouldn't get you too bad.

01:16:19.870 --> 01:16:20.810
It's an error message.

01:16:20.810 --> 01:16:21.600
This is better.

01:16:21.600 --> 01:16:23.300
Same error, but a little bit more text.

01:16:23.440 --> 01:16:25.760
And finally,
this is the best way to communicate.

01:16:25.760 --> 01:16:28.930
So that's designing the interface.

01:16:28.940 --> 01:16:33.530
It all matters because it generates
high customer productivity when your

01:16:33.650 --> 01:16:36.850
